  "prompt": "How do I know viewers of my Facebook profile?",
  "response": "Facebook does not provide a feature that allows you to see exactly who has viewed your profile. This is to protect user privacy. However, there are a few things you can do to get some insights:\n\n1. **Insights for Pages**: If you have a Facebook Page (not a personal profile), you can use Facebook Insights to see page views, but they won't tell you exactly who viewed your page.\n\n2. **Engagement Metrics**: You can check likes, comments, and shares on your posts to see who is interacting with your content.\n\n3. **Friendship Suggestions**: Facebook sometimes suggests friends based on mutual interactions, but this is not a direct indicator of who viewed your profile.\n\n4. **Third-Party Apps**: Be cautious of third-party apps claiming to show profile viewers. These are often scams or violate Facebook's terms of service.\n\nIf you're concerned about privacy:\n\n- **Privacy Settings**: Regularly review your privacy settings to control who can see your posts and profile information.\n- **Blocking**: You can block specific users if you don't want them to see your profile.\n\nAlways remember, Facebook's policies are designed to protect user privacy, so direct methods to see profile viewers are not available.",
